        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "A current workaround is to overwrite the ui2 `cmdline_*` handlers with the custom handlers being used before ui2, and not attaching to ext_cmdline ourselves at all.\nWhere I previously had:\n\n```lua\nvim.ui_attach(cmdline.ns, { ext_cmdline = true }, function(...)\n    if event == \"cmdline_show\" then\n        custom_cmdline_show(...)\n    end\n)\n```\n\nBecomes instead:\n```lua\nlocal ui = require(\"vim._core.ui2\")\nui.enable({...})\nui.cmd.cmdline_show = custom_cmdline_show\n```\n\nCustom handlers might of course need changes to work with ui2, but this allows keeping the new message behavior while using a custom command line. Popup menu handlers stay in ui_attach",
            "created_at": "2026-04-10T18:18:33Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38916#issuecomment-4225835876",
            "id": 4225835876,
